Green Curry Paste
  --Julia Mueller

1/2 c fresh basil, chopped
1/2 c fresh cilantro, chopped
1 stalk lemongrass, thinly sliced (or 3 tbsp Lemongrass paste)
2 jalape√±os, seeded and chopped
1 medium shallot, chopped
5 cloves garlic, minced
1 tbsp fresh ginger, grated
1/2 tsp ground cumin
1/2 tsp ground coriander
1 tbsp coconut aminos *, or low-sodium soy sauce
zest of 1 lime
2 tsp fresh lime juice
4-6 tbsp full-fat canned coconut milk

Add all ingredients except for the coconut milk to a blender or food processor. Pulse until everything is finely chopped. Add the coconut milk a couple of tablespoons at a time and continue blending until a paste is achieved.


Notes: I didn't add the coconut milk
